IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE MISSION OF TALL TIMBERS RESEARCH, INC. IS TO FOSTER EXEMPLARY LAND STEWARDSHIP THROUGH RESEARCH, CONSERVATION AND EDUCATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF TALL TIMBERS RESEARCH,INC. IS TO FOSTER EXEMPLARY LAND STEWARDSHIP THROUGH RESEARCH, CONSERVATION AND EDUCATION.OUR PRIMARY RESEARCH FOCUS IS THE ECOLOGY OF FIRE AND NATURAL RESOURCE MANAGEMENT INCLUDING BOBWHITE QUAIL AND OTHER WILDLIFE IN THE SOUTHEASTERN COASTAL PLAIN. OUR CONSERVATION EFFORTS ARE DEDICATED TO HELPING PROTECT THE DISTINCTIVE RED HILLS LANDSCAPE OF SOUTH GEORGIA AND NORTH FLORIDA, AND ITS TRADITIONAL LAND USES. OUR EDUCATION PROGRAM TRANSFERS RESEARCH AND CONSERVATION INFORMATION FOR RESOURCE MANAGEMENT.DEFINING EXEMPLARY LAND STEWARDSHIP EXEMPLARY LAND STEWARDSHIP (ELS) BALANCES ECOLOGICAL VALUES AND ECONOMIC UTILITY WITHIN A FRAMEWORK OF LONG-TERM CONSERVATION. THE FOUNDATION OF ELS ON UPLAND HABITATS IN THE RED HILLS IS THE FREQUENT USE OF FIRE TO ACCOMMODATE MANAGEMENT FOR BOBWHITE QUAIL, SELECTION TIMBER HARVEST, AND OTHER TRADITIONAL LAND USES. SCENIC, OPEN MULTI-AGED FOREST STRUCTURES ARE FUNDAMENTAL TO ELS.
IRS990.Desc: QUAIL MANAGEMENT RESEARCH MONITORED RADIO-TAGGED BOBWHITES AS PART OF STUDIES ON POPULATION DYNAMICS ON NORTHERN BOBWHITE IN GA, FL, SC, NC, AND NJ; TRANSLOCATED WILD BOBWHITES TO 5 SITES ACROSS THE SOUTHEASTERN AND MID-ATLANTIC U.S. TO ESTABLISH NEW POPULATIONS AND CONDUCT RESEARCH IN RELATION TO SUCH; WE CONTINUED OUR STUDIES ON BOBWHITE SURVIVAL RATES IN RELATION TO COVER MANAGEMENT, COVEY MOVEMENTS IN RELATION TO HUNTING PRESSURE, AND WILD TURKEY MOVEMENTS IN RELATION TO SUPPLEMENTAL FEEDING; CONDUCTED 2 BOBWHITE DOG FIELD TRIALS, PUBLISHED 2 MANAGEMENT NEWSLETTERS, MONITORED BOBWHITE ON COLLABORATIVE FOREST RESTORATION LANDSCAPE PROJECT ON OSCEOLA NATIONAL FOREST AND ON 4 SITES IN FLORIDA ON PUBLIC LANDS TOTALING 100,000 ACRES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: STAFF MADE 35 SCIENTIFIC PRESENTATIONS AT CONFERENCES, SEMINARS AND WORKSHOPS, AND REACHED OVER 4300 PROFESSIONALS THROUGH 156 OUTREACH ACTIVITIES. PUBLISHED 12 SCIENTIFIC MANUSCRIPTS RELATED TO FIRE ECOLOGY AND MANAGEMENT; CONTINUED BEHAVIOR ECOLOGY OF BROWN-HEADED NUTHATCHES; CONTINUED PRESCRIBED FIRE PM RESEARCH MONITORING AND MODELLING, CONTINUED LONG-TERM FIRE PLOT RESEARCH IN NATIVE GROUND COVER, COMPLETED HISTORICAL RECORDS FOR THE FIRE USE ON OLD GROWTH FORESTS, ESTABLISHED AN ON-LINE HERBARIUM RESOURCE, HOSTED REGIONAL MESSAGING WORKSHOP FOR PRESCRIBED FIRE, TRAINED FIRE PROFESSIONALS ON PRESCRIBED FIRE METHODS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: IN 2015, TALL TIMBERS CLOSED ON A 1,389 ACRE CONSERVATION EASEMENT FOR HICKORY GROVE PLANTATION IN MACON COUNTY, GEORGIA. IN ADDITION, TALL TIMBERS SUCCESSFULLY RECEIVED UNANIMOUS SUPPORT FROM THE SUWANNEE RIVER WATER MANAGEMENT DISTRICT (SRWMD) TO START THE LAND ACQUISITION PROCESS FOR SAVING A MATURE GROWTH CYPRESS TRACT ADJACENT TO SNEADS SMOKEHOUSE RECREATIONAL AREA ALONG THE AUCILLA RIVER IN JEFFERSON COUNTY, FLORIDA. A GOPHER TORTOISE SPECIES SURVEY WAS CONDUCTED IN THE GREATER RED HILLS REGION. THE EIGHT-MONTH SURVEY EXAMINED 34,000 ACRES OF PRIVATE LAND, AND THE FINDINGS CONCLUDED THAT THE REGION SUPPORTS AN ESTIMATED 23,000 TORTOISES, REFLECTING A HEALTHY POPULATION. FINALLY, TALL TIMBERS JOINED THE LAND TRUST ALLIANCE IN AN OUTREACH EFFORT TO SECURE PASSAGE OF THE FEDERAL ENHANCED TAX INCENTIVES FOR DONATED CONSERVATION EASEMENTS, WHICH WAS MADE PERMANENT AND SIGNED INTO LAW.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MODIFICATION 1: FAIR OAKS PLANTATION CONSERVATION EASEMENT - A SUBSTANTIVE AMENDMENT THAT UPDATED THE ACCESSORY BUILDING LIST FOR THE RECONSTRUCTED MAIN HOME, GRANTED TALL TIMBERS ALL OVERSIGHT FOR ALL MAIN HOUSE IMPROVEMENTS AND CONSTRUCTION (REMOVED 3RD PARTY OVERSIGHT), UPDATED RECOMMENDED REFERENCE DOCUMENTS FOR THE MAIN HOME, MODIFIED THE PUBLIC ACCESS REQUIREMENT, AND MODIFIED FISHING RIGHTS BY REMOVING DECEASED INDIVIDUALS. MODIFICATION 2: HICKORY HEAD CORRECTIVE CONSERVATION EASEMENT - THE ORIGINAL CONSERVATION EASEMENT CONTAINED MUTUAL MISTAKES AND THE CORRECTIVE CONSERVATION EASEMENT REMEDIES THE MISTAKES AND RESTATES THE TERMS OF THE CONSERVATION EASEMENT. MODIFICATION 3: PINCKNEY HILL CORRECTIVE CONSERVATION EASEMENT - THE ORIGINAL CONSERVATION EASEMENT HAD A MISTAKE IN THE LEGAL DESCRIPTION OF THE PROPERTY AND INCLUDED 15 ACRES THAT WERE NOT OWNED BY THE ORIGINAL GRANTOR. THE CORRECTIVE CONSERVATION EASEMENT REMOVED THE 15 ACRES FROM THE LEGAL DESCRIPTION. TRANSFERRED: 0 RELEASED: 0 EXTINGUISHED: 0 TERMINATED: 0

TALL TIMBERS ENFORCEMENT OF EASEMENTS POLICY, APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES ON APRIL 8, 2008, INCLUDES STANDARDS AND PROCEDURES CONSISTENT WITH THOSE ESTABLISHED BY THE LAND TRUST STANDARDS AND PRACTICES AND THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE POLICY COMPLEMENTS THE TALL TIMBERS MODEL LEGAL EASEMENT, ARTICLE III, ENFORCEMENT AND REMEDIES SECTION. THE POLICY OUTLINES PROCEDURES FOR ENFORCEMENT OF BOTH MINOR VIOLATIONS AND MAJOR VIOLATIONS, AND INCLUDES DEFINITIONS OF BOTH TERMS. IT ALSO OUTLINES COURSES OF ACTION FOR COMPLIANCE, AND REFERENCES THE LEGAL EASEMENT FOR TIMELINES, INSPECTIONS, AND ALTERNATIVES TO LEGAL ACTION SUCH AS ARBITRATION OR MEDIATION. THE TALL TIMBERS MODEL LEGAL EASEMENT ENFORCEMENT PROVISIONS ARE INCLUDED IN TALL TIMBERS EASEMENTS. IN ADDITION, TALL TIMBERS HAS AN INTERNAL CONSERVATION EASEMENT MONITORING PROCEDURE WHICH OUTLINES MONITORING FREQUENCY (ANNUALLY) AND PROCESS.

GIFTS OF CONSERVATION AND SCENIC EASEMENTS ARE GRANTED TO THE ORGANIZATION BY PROPERTY OWNERS. THESE EASEMENTS RESTRICT THE USE OF THE LAND AND SOME ALLOW THE ORGANIZATION TO CONDUCT RESEARCH AND STUDIES ON THE PROPERTIES. SINCE THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT ACQUIRE ANY RIGHTS TO THE PROPERTY, NO VALUE IS RECORDED FOR THESE EASEMENTS.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS MUSEUM FURNITURE MAINTAINED AT THE HENRY BEADEL HOUSE. THESE ITEMS ARE KEPT ON DISPLAY FOR TOURS OF THE TALL TIMBERS RESEARCH STATION AND HENRY BEADEL HOUSE. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO MAINTAINS A SCIENTIFIC COLLECTION USED IN EDUCATION AND RESEARCH.

THE FASB ISSUED GUIDANCE THAT REQUIRES TAX EFFECTS FROM AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION TO BE RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ONLY IF THE POSITION IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT TO BE SUSTAINED IF THE POSITION WERE TO BE CHALLENGED BY A TAXING AUTHORITY. THE ASSESSMENT OF THE TAX POSITION IS BASED SOLELY ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION, WITHOUT REGARD TO THE LIKELIHOOD THAT THE TAX POSITION MAY BE CHALLENGED. IF AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION MEETS THE MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT THRESHOLD, THE LARGEST AMOUNT OF TAX BENEFIT THAT IS GREATER THAN 50% LIKELY TO BE RECOGNIZED UPON ULTIMATE SETTLEMENT WITH THE TAXING AUTHORITY IS RECORDED. TALL TIMBERS RESEARCH IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX UNDER IRC SECTION 501(C) (3), THOUGH IT IS SUBJECT TO TAX ON INCOME UNRELATED TO ITS EXEMPT PURPOSES, UNLESS THAT INCOME IS OTHERWISE EXCLUDED BY THE IRC. THERE ARE NO TAX POSITIONS FOR WHICH A MATERIAL CHANGE IN ANY UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFIT LIABILITY IS REASONABLY POSSIBLE IN THE NEXT 12 MONTHS. THERE IS NO INTEREST OR PENALTIES RECOGNIZED IN THE INCOME STATEMENT OR BALANCE SHEET. FEDERAL RETURNS FOR THE TAX YEARS ENDING 2012, 2013 AND 2014, ARE STILL OPEN TO AUDIT. THIS GUIDANCE DID NOT HAVE ANY IMPACT ON THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
